    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#marengo2010a"/>, p. 150, n. <citedRange>5</citedRange>; fig. 2.5</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>60.1841.2</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>111800</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#santucci1998"/>, pp. <citedRange>525, 530</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Τιμ_"><seg part="I"><abbr>Τιμ</abbr></seg></name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Tim<gap reason="omitted"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré cette coupe.</supplied></p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Tim<gap reason="omitted"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this cup.</supplied></p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Tim<gap reason="omitted"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questa coppa.</supplied></p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This sherd was found along with those bearing <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr088400</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr088500</ref> (personal 
                    communication by A. Santucci).</p>
                <p>The letters can be interpreted as the beginning of many personal names, such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Τιμαγόρας</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Τίμαρχος</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Τιμῶναξ</foreign>.</p>
                <p>Another possibility of expansion for those three letters would be the word <foreign xml:lang="grc">τιμά</foreign>, usual in price inscriptions;
                    however Marengo excludes that because no numeral follows.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
